{% extends 'base.html.j2' %}

{% block head %}

{% endblock %}
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
{% block body %}
<header class="blog-title">
    <h1><b>Welcome To My Website!</b></h1>
    <p>Maybe it's a blog, maybe it's for hosting projects, maybe it's just an excuse to play with some web frameworks and libraries. 
        I don't really know what it's for yet, but there should be some cool stuff here, so feel free to have a look around. Oh, and here's a bird:</p>
    <h3>Your Bird:</br>{{ bird_name }}
        <p style="font-style: italic; margin: 0; font-weight: normal;">(Images retrieved from <a href="https://ebird.org/home">ebird.org</a>)</p>
    </h3>
    {% if bird_image in 'https://cdn.download.ams.birds.cornell.edu/api/v1/asset//1200' %}
        <img src="{{ url_for('static', filename='Images/image_missing.jpg') }}" width="300em" height="auto">
    {% else %}
        <img src="{{ bird_image }}" width="300em" height="auto">
    {% endif %}
    </br>
    <a href="/bird_scraper">What is this?</a></br>
    <a href="{{ bird_url }}">More about this bird</a></br>
</header>
{% endblock %}